    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p><a href=\"http://java.sun.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/util/TreeMap.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>TreeMap</code></a> is an example of a <a href=\"http://java.sun.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/util/SortedMap.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>SortedMap</code></a>, which means that the order of the keys can be sorted, and when iterating over the keys, you can expect that they will be in order.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://java.sun.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/util/HashMap.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>HashMap</code></a> on the other hand, makes no such guarantee.  Therefore, when iterating over the keys of a <code>HashMap</code>, you can't be sure what order they will be in.</p>\n\n<p><code>HashMap</code> will be more efficient in general, so use it whenever you don't care about the order of the keys.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "user_type" : "does_not_exist",
      "display_name" : "user8681"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 8,
    "last_activity_date" : 1268611364,
