    "creation_date" : 1370956071,
    "answer_id" : 17044901,
    "question_id" : 2444359,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>To sum up:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>HashMap: Lookup-array structure, based on hashCode(), equals() implementations, O(1) runtime complexity for inserting and searching, unsorted</li>\n<li>TreeMap: Tree structure, based on compareTo() implementation, O(log(N)) runtime complexity for inserting and searching, sorted</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Taken from: <a href=\"http://arnosoftwaredev.blogspot.com/2010/10/hash-tables-vs-binary-search-tree.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\" title=\"HashMap vs. TreeMap\">HashMap vs. TreeMap</a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 169237,
        "reputation" : 40334,
        "user_id" : 395202,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "accept_rate" : 59,
        "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/c422b640dd62b019c125836b1059e231?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
        "display_name" : "Adrian Shum",
