      "comment_id" : 26635321,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Not necessary.  If you really want this, you can simply make a decorator for a map, for which for all things involving key input, you make it all upper/lower case, and delegate to the decorated map.  By doing so, it is not that difficult to have a &quot;case insensitive&quot; hashmap.  Anyway, this answer is probably a bit off-topic: you are only talking about a very specific use case of treemap, for which I don&#39;t see it being very meaningful as a comparison between hashmap/treemap"
    } ],
    "owner" : {
